# Common Mistakes

### Mistake 1

Thinking the bucket index is the hash code itself.

---

### Mistake 2

Assuming all 32 bits of the hash determine the bucket.

---

### Mistake 3

Believing hash spreading eliminates collisions.

It **reduces** collisions but cannot eliminate them entirely.

---

### Mistake 4

Confusing the unsigned right shift operator (`>>>`) with the signed right shift operator (`>>`).

