# 60-Second Revision

- `HashMap` mixes higher bits into lower bits using `h ^ (h >>> 16)`.
- Bucket index uses `hash & (tableLength - 1)`.
- Only lower bits determine the bucket.
- Hash spreading reduces collisions by improving the quality of the lower bits.
- It is a lightweight optimization that significantly improves key distribution.

